Remarks.
The present new species is very remarkable in having a strongly gibbous carapace. Other features that can be used to separate this species from the other species of the genus are: 
1
) wide lateral rostral lamina reaching almost to tip of rostrum; 
2
) shorter and less wide fingers of pereiopod I; 
3
) stouter ambulatory pereiopods and 
4
) stouter telson with dorsal spines situated close to its distal margin.
